body:
Verilator does not allow DPI-C imported tasks cannot pass simulation time, else they get deadlocked as per this issue: #4225, unlike other simulators (Vivado xsim...).

### My use case:
I am building an SV design that runs on the FPGA & controlled by the host ARM processor running a custom C firmware. I am using Verilator and Vivado Xsim to test them together in simulation. I have built the firmware as a set of C functions, and I call them from a main SystemVerilog testbench via DPI-C.

Everything works fine, except writing into an AXI-lite register bank from the C firmware. Since the register bank is in SystemVerilog and not memory mapped to C's memory space, I need to export an SV function/task, import it in C, and use it to read & write to the register. But **writing to AXI-Lite register takes one or more clock cycles**, and the SV task I import in C cannot pass time, due to the above Verilator issue.

### Workaround

My current workaround is to directly update the memory in SV function, bypassing AXI-Lite as follows:

#### SV testbench
```sv
export "DPI-C" function get_config;
export "DPI-C" function set_config;
function integer get_config(input integer offset);
  return dut.axi_lite_controller.cfg[offset];
endfunction

function void set_config(input integer offset, input integer data);
  dut.axi_lite_controller.cfg[offset] = data;
endfunction
```

#### C firmware
```c
#ifdef SIM
  extern int32_t get_config(int32_t offset);
  extern void set_config(int32_t offset, int32_t data);
#else // when running on FPGA
  int32_t get_config(int32_t offset){
    return *((int32_t*)(CONFIG_BASEADDR + offset));
  }
  void set_config(int32_t offset, int32_t data){	
    *((int32_t*)(CONFIG_BASEADDR + offset)) = data;
  }
#endif

void runtime() {
 // ...
 int conf3 = get_config(3);
 set_config(3, 27);
 // ...
}
```

### Problem:

But this does not verify the AXI-Lite pipeline, which makes me uncomfortable. Is there a way I can call `get_config(offset)` and `set_config(offset, data)` from C, to read & write from AXI-Lite register bank?
